  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Finance Executive (Township)",
  "description": "<p>Reporting to the Senior Finance Manager, you shall monitor and comply with financial reporting guidelines, prepare and review annual budget, prepare financial statements, perform budgetary controls and manage arrears. You shall be required to ensure proper records of transactions and drive strong financial controls. In addition, you are responsible for grants and assets management, inter-funds transfers, tax reporting etc.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements: </strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Accounting/Finance/ACCA with minimum 5 - 8 years of relevant experiences in full-set accounting  </li>\n  <li>Strong analytical thought process and able to handle tight timeline and stress</li>\n  <li>Meticulous and can work independently and as a team player</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in MS Office applications (Excel, Words)</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in staff management</li>\n  <li>Able to start within a short period will be preferred</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Employment Type: 2-years contract (renewable) with benefits</p>\n<p>Working Location: Northwest - Bukit Gombak</p>\n<p>Work Schedule: 5-day work week, is required to work half-day on the first Saturday of each month</p>",
